main event: On November 16, 1956 in Fox River Grove, Illinois, a UFO was observed. The object was initially described as dull red, changed in size and shape, and appeared to move at high speeds before disappearing into the distance.
interesting points: The object was observed hovering for five minutes before accelerating quickly to at least 1000 m.p.h. in a southeast to north course.
The conclusion indicated that the sighting could possibly be a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object, but there was insufficient data to fully evaluate the sighting.
The witness estimated the object's speed at around 1000 m.p.h. and described it as moving horizontally to the east and disappearing at a 45-degree angle to the horizon in about 3 to 4 seconds.
The witness mentioned observing three small round objects coming from an outer dark part of the sky and merging into a cigar-shaped object.
The witness noted that the object appeared to be metal, big, and rough in shape, with engines, instruments, and the ability to change from a round shape to a streamlined cigar shape.
result: Possibly a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object with insufficient data for evaluation
sighted object: Unidentified object which changed in size and shape, and appeared to move at high speeds
witnesses: The witness provided a detailed description and estimated the object's speed and behavior
